   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In your org, go to Object Manager and search for Power Template (APXTPower4__Power_Template__c)</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Go to Fields and Relationships, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New</uicontrol> and select Text for the field type. Give it the label "Old ID" and a Length value of 255.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Determine the Visibility of the field, ensure that at minimum System Administrators have access to the new Old ID field. It does not have to be added to the Page Layout. Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Copy the API name of the Field (Old_ID__c) and go to your extracted file for your Templates.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Find the ID field in the document and paste the Old_ID__c value over the ID column header.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="912"
                         href="../attachments/231212826/231212819.jpg"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open Salesforce Data Loader, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Insert</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If your template Name field contains a "-" in the label (example: CQT-0004), you may run into problems with Data Loader. To work around this, navigate to Salesforce Data Loader &gt; Settings and confirm that "Read all CSVs with UTF-8 encoding" is enabled, and remove the "-" from the "Other Delimiters for load operations". </p>
                  <p class="- topic/p ">It is also recommended to enable "Use Bulk API". </p>
               </note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the Power Template (APXTPower4__Power_Template__c) object, then select your file to import it.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the Mapping popup, click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Create a Map</uicontrol> button, then drag and drop your fields to map them to the correct column header. Most importantly, map the Old_ID__c field to the Old_ID__c field.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image height="400"
                         placement="break"
                         href="../attachments/231212826/231212820.jpg"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Save your mapping to your local machine and click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Finish</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the Finish popup, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Browse</uicontrol> to choose where your Results file will appear. Begin the Import.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Once completed, click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">View Successes</uicontrol> button, then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Open in external program</uicontrol> to receive a new Success Export file.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
